Data

All participants included in this analysis had PTA > 25 in the better ear, with complete data across 28 predictors of interest (n=756).

Note: After dropping the first Age Stigma item (Q4), 3 more observations with complete data were added (they had been missing Q4 data), increasing the total sample size from n=753 to n=756.

Bars are now labelled with counts, to highlight that on scales with multiple categories, few people tended to choose the most extreme negative option.
